value: potatoe stalks & other tender vegetables were frozen but not to any great extent.
no agitation could be discovered as i was in a canoe and on the water at the time. it passed me at 7am. on the 30th [illegible, reads: int] there was only small pieces of ice remaining in the lakes

search being made none of it ravages among threes [misspelling of ‘trees’?] or any other object could be discovered. it [went?] in a westerly direction from this place, say six miles and passed within a mile of where i was.

the ice in the lakes began to shift about with the wind on the 27th. i heard a whirlwind on 28th. i was not close enough to see it but the noise it made was tremendous, something resembling the noise of a large fall of water. it came from north and went in a southerly direction.
during december there were seventeen days snow
during this month there were sixteen days snow. snow birds were first seen on 16th. little rivers begin to open on 30th
during this month there were seven days of snow. the average depth of snow which fell during intervals was 3 1/2 feet.
